{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43cdc252-e795-4c53-a3b2-950002595495","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0` — only `net8.0+`, `net462`, and `uap10.0` are supported.\n\nYou **must retarget to `net8.0` or later** before upgrading to MSTest v4.\n\nYour test code itself (simple `[TestClass]`/`[TestMethod]` with `Assert.IsTrue`) should be fine — no breaking API changes affect it. The only blocker is the TFM.\n\n**To upgrade**, you'd need to:\n1. Change `<TargetFramework>` from `net6.0` → `net8.0` (or `net9.0`)\n2. Then update the MSTest package from `3.8.0` → `4.x`\n\nWould you like me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65b3a2d5-c72a-463c-87a9-ce848f8bc00c","outputTokens":208},"id":"9fa1400c-71a1-433f-ab40-a438fca90905","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:58.375Z","parentId":"d24b7f19-a94d-4481-a36d-aaaa50f23ad8"}
